In February, the Federal Parliament passed a motion I moved to recognise this day. Here is my short statement commemorating those lives lost either through miscarriage, stillbirth, or perinatal death. 
(Start of thread)

In Australia, 1 in 4 pregnancies ends in miscarriage.  6 babies a day are stillborn.  Perinatal death – the death of a baby in the weeks just before, during or just after birth – numbers around 3000 a year in Australia – and of those deaths, 2,200 are stillborn.
